headline: Centene’s 2025 Loss and 2026 Outlook Could Be A Game Changer For Centene (CNC)
summary: In early February 2026, Centene Corporation reported fourth-quarter 2025 revenue of US$49.73 billion and a net loss of US$1.10 billion, with full-year 2025 revenue of US$194.78 billion and a net loss of US$6.67 billion, alongside guidance for 2026 GAAP diluted EPS above US$1.98 and total revenues of US$186.50 billion to US$190.50 billion. The sharp swing from prior-year profitability to a large full-year loss, despite higher revenue and expectations for margin improvement in 2026, highlights...
